14/08/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov on Thursday (August 13th) scheduled the interim mayoral elections in Sofia and Vratsa for November 15th. The post in Sofia became vacant after incumbent Boyko Borisov became prime minister. His Citizens for the European Development of Bulgaria (GERB) party won the general elections in July. The mayor of the northern city of Vratsa, Totyu Mladenov, was appointed labour minister in the new government. (Dnevnik, bTV, BTA, Capital - 13/08/09)
